                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>This inscription is dated in the 16th year of the reign of the ancient <hi rend="bold">Chōḷa</hi> king <hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman</hi>,<note>To the same reign belong Nos. <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv01p0i0085">85</ref> and <ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv01p0i0148">148</ref> of Vol. I. The king is perhaps identical with Vijayālaya, the grandfather of Parāntaka I.</note> and records that the villagers granted certain land to the temple, at the request and with the approval of the temple manager, <hi rend="bold">Chakrapāṇi Nambi</hi> (ll. 3 and 10).</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
